handNote.desc:
Ancient palaeographical features: 
ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line; 
ቍ has the labiovelar marker attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line; 
መ, ሠ, ቆ, ቶ, ዐ have angular shape; 
the left strokes of ለ and ዘ are slanted.

 Some palaoegraphical features: 
 መ, ሠ, የ, and ጸ have angular shapes; 
 ሐ has squared shape; 
 ቆ, ቶ, ደ, and ፀ have sometimes angular shape; 
the letters ግ and ዚ are written together in the word እግዚአብሔር.
